subSubSection.paragraph:
Adult females differ from holotype in having a grayish brown vertebral stripe, fading away posteriorly, and grayish brown flanks (Fig. 
14
). Juvenile QCAZ 16350 differs from holotype in having grayish brown flanks, without scattered dark brown spots; juvenile QCAZ 16351 is unique in having white spots on flanks and over forelimbs.
